Only 1 point for greatest work of CG department. Gaps:
- stupid plot
- clip storytelling
- poor characters
- exploitation of favorite things from 1-6 episodes
- creative impotence
- skype force (are you kidding me??). In this case Palpatine can kill everyone in the galaxy staying home in every episode
- incompetent J. J. Abrams and Kathleen Kennedy

Hope it's the last SW movie by Disney
I really loved this episode.  I've been watching Star Wars movies from the beginning and think this was one of the best.  If you are a fan, it is a must see.
After the disaster that was episode 8, JJ did the the best with what he was handed. The movie was good in that regard

Didn't want to see this after Disney's two previous attempts at killing the franchise. I'll have to say it was better than expected (Disney set a very low bar).  There was an attempt to tell a story and not just preach wokeness to us however, the characters were still 1D and dialog was predictable and tiring. the visuals were great as usual.
Liked the movie , could have been better written but loved all the answers we got to the years old questions . Was “ Star Wars funny”
Not perfect. But infinitely better than TLJ. Probably the best one since the original trilogy.
I thought pulling in past characters as they did was very effectively done.  The special effects were again superb. I thought the acting was very good.

Superb! How this can only have 54% rating whilst The Last Jedi has 91% is beyond me! It's almost like the critics are making up for giving the former such a high score. Don't get me wrong I loved TLJ, but this is much better!

After Rian Johnson derailed the series with episode 8, leaving it completely disjointed and full of loose ends, Abrams had the impossible task of ending Star Wars on a high note. He did an admirable job of reinfusing the galaxy with the panacea of myth while doing justice to all the major character arcs. All told, The Rise of Skywalker is epic storytelling on a massive scale.
